THREE bodies of middle aged men were discovered in a bush near Nwamatatani in Limpopo. A person who was passing by noticed the body of an unknown man lying in the bushes and notified the police. Police spokesperson Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe said upon arrival at the crime scene, the police discovered two more bodies lying dead with gunshot wounds. Ngoepe said the men have not yet been identified. He said the motive behind these killings is also unknown at this stage but the police investigations are still unfolding. According to Ngoepe the suspects are unknown and no arrest have been made yet. Ngoepe urged anyone with information which can lead to the arrest of the suspects and who can assist the police in the identification of all the three deceased to contact Captain Rhulani Masotja at 082 468 8673 or the crime stop number 0860010111.